                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Higgins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-08T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 8, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>190. Reference first paragraph my telegram No. 188 of December 6 [<hi
                        rend="italic">7</hi>], noon, Minister of Foreign Affairs has twice again
                    requested me to ascertain as soon as possible if Department will recognize
                    present government in Salvador. He is impatient for early information as his
                    Government’s action will be in conformity with that of the United States and he
                    is being strongly pressed to announce his Government’s decision.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Higgins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
